snippet.title: ‚ÄòEveryone told me it would end my career‚Äô: Amber Heard opens up about coming out as bisexual
snippet.description:
New Delhi, March 26 (ANI): She came out publicly about her bisexuality in 2010 and now, Amber Heard has opened up about how difficult it was. Speaking at The Economist's Pride & Prejudice event at New York, the ‚ÄòDanish Girl‚Äô star claimed that the filmmakers doubted whether she could play a straight woman in a romantic lead, reports The Independent. Heard was quoted saying, ‚ÄúIt was not easy. I was the only one working in this way, so it was definitely difficult because no one had done it.‚Äù The 30-year-old actress added, "I did that even though everyone told me it would end my career, without a doubt." The actress also shared about her "coming out" announcement and why she never hid her sexuality. ‚ÄúWhen I hear someone comment about me coming out, I think it's funny because I was never in. Then I realised the gravity of what I had done.‚Äù On a related note, Amber Heard will be next seen in Zack Snyder‚Äôs ‚ÄòJustice League‚Äô alongside Ben Affleck.
